[STEP 2] The base case for the DP is `dp[0] = True` since a single element array is already split. The DP transition would involve iterating through all possible split points `j` from 0 to `i-1`. We would check if `dp[j]` is true, meaning `nums[0...j]` can be split, and if the sum of `nums[j+1...i]` is either length 1 or >= m. If both conditions are met, then `dp[i]` is true.

[STEP 3] The naive DP approach would have a time complexity of O(n^2) since we have a nested loop for iterating through the split points. To optimize, we can precompute the prefix sums to calculate the sum of `nums[j+1...i]` in O(1) time. This will keep the overall complexity at O(n^2).

